HEADWORD: Protamin
<hw>Pro"ta*min</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>prw^tos</grk> first.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>An
amorphous nitrogenous substance found in the spermatic fluid of salmon.
It is soluble in water, which an alkaline reaction, and unites with
acids and metallic bases.</def>⟦br⟧
